r> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> We are RUSHING you this update because the Ninth Circuit Court of Appeals just ruled the Pledge Of Allegiance <br>
unconstitutional in our public schools! <br>
The judges ruled that the phrase &quot;under God&quot; is a violation <br>
of the U.S. Constitution because it creates an &quot;establishment&quot; <br>
of religion. <br>
THIS IS OUTRAGEOUS!!! WE MUST TAKE ACTION!</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
 Sorry, I'll fight this in any way I can. It's about bloody time somebody took this step.<br>
<br>
 First, Ben, get it right. Don't spread falsehoods in your haste. They did <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>not</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> outlaw the pledge of alliegance. They only declared the bits about &quot;God&quot; to be unconstitutional.<br>
<br>
The fact that &quot;Dog&quot; is mentioned on money, and in the declaration, and in oaths is taken to mean that it's all right, that it's supposed to be there.<br>
 <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>no</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> sorry, wrong. These are all just other cases of the encroachment on our freedoms. The recent decision should only be the first of many steps to set it right.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> &quot;The United States is in no way founded upon the Christian religion.&quot; --George Washington and John Adams, Diplomatic message to Malta<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
 Just because they were all from nations with some form of christianity, and they all might have claimed some form of faith, just remember this: They established among the 10 most important rights to be protected from the government, that freedon of whatever religious belief you want, is important.<br>
<br>
 <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> &quot;Christians go home!&quot;</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Send 'em all back to the mideast, where there are plenty of religious states. What? All the land is taken up? Sounds like it's time for another holy war... Y'all are out of practise in that -it used to be a time-honored part of forcing your beliefs on others.<br>
